WRASM's own crates — `rasm`, `was`, `ide`, `winkb`, `studio`, and the supporting
`docpane` and `rust-tcl` — are Copyright (c) 2024-2026 Alban Read under the MIT
License above; they are first-party, not third-party. `rust-tcl` is an original,
Tcl-inspired command-language core (not derived from Tcl/Tk source). The
components listed below are external open-source dependencies.

WRASM links (and, for SQLite, embeds) open-source software. The complete and
authoritative dependency set is pinned in `Cargo.lock`; the principal components
and their licenses are listed below. Except where noted, each is used under the
MIT License (the same terms reproduced above). Components offered as
"MIT OR Apache-2.0" are used under the MIT option; the Apache-2.0 alternative is
available at https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.

